						<summary>

						<p>A portion at the right end of this inscription is damaged. Registers the gift by the king of taxes <hi rend="italic">(kaḍamai)</hi> on a village to the temple of Saṉṉavaṉamuḍaiya Nāyaṇār at Tiruttiyūr muṭṭam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Sundarapāṇḍya chatūrvēdimaṅgalam in Talaiyūrnāḍu. It also mentions the taxes imposed and collected according to the yield from the lands such as 1(1/4) on <hi rend="italic">Puñjai</hi> and 25 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> from the <hi rend="italic">Nattam</hi> land etc.</p>						

						</summary>
